      <intermediateExchange id="89fa57ef-9329-598f-a1a4-0f1934a95090" unitId="2f4daad7-5331-4f14-930c-d8bca924557d" amount="0.190946456" intermediateExchangeId="cfbce515-3f54-4411-ad9d-3d26b7faa15a" activityLinkId="27b7258c-5742-5ce9-a2e3-ca7f7a862856">
        <name xml:lang="en">transport, freight, lorry, unspecified</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">metric ton*km</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Estimated value, assuming average European transport distances as a proxy for Quebec. European distance derived as follows: Transport distance based on eurostat transport statistics for road freight transport. The transport data was extracted from the database leaf 'Road transport &gt; Road freight transport measurement &gt; Total road freight transport &gt; Road freight transport by type of goods and type of transport (t, tkm) - annual data (ROAD_GO_TA_TG)' (https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/databrowser/) on 2023-08-02. The transport distance was calculated based on the total mass of goods transported (t) and total payload-distance (t*km) for the NST 2007 category 'GT06 - Wood and products of wood and cork (except furniture); articles of straw and plaiting materials; pulp, paper and paper products; printed matter and recorded media' in the year 2016 for all countries for which data was available. The average distance of road transport for goods in this category in 2016 was 209 km. The fraction of goods transported by road (in terms of mass) relative to the total mass of goods transported by road, rail and inland waterways was 91% in 2016. Therefore, the average distance that goods travelled by road in 2016 was 191 km. This value is assumed to be representative for Europe.</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="0.190946456" mu="-1.6557622253152646" variance="0.12" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.20320000000000002"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="2" completeness="3" temporalCorrelation="5" geographicalCorrelation="5" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="4"/>
        </uncertainty>
